# ProjectFlo — Validation Conventions

## Backend (NestJS)
- Validate all request bodies and query params with DTOs using `class-validator`.
- Apply `ValidationPipe({ transform: true })` in controllers on `@Body()` and `@Query()` so types are coerced (e.g. query string → number).
- DTO rules:
  - Every field has at least one validation decorator.
  - Optional fields: `@IsOptional()` first, then type decorator.
  - Nested objects: `@ValidateNested()` + `@Type(() => NestedDto)`.
  - Query numeric fields: `@Type(() => Number)` + `@IsNumber()`.
  - One DTO class per file; no `any` properties.
- DTOs validate shape/type only; business rules belong in services and should throw `BadRequestException`.

## Frontend
- Validate required fields before submitting; show field-level errors using MUI `TextField` (`error` + `helperText`).
- Do not silently discard invalid input; keep validation logic in a dedicated function (not inline in the submit handler).

